MKP Support Electron (MKPSupportE) End User License Agreement (EULA)

Update Date: March 10, 2026
Effective Date: March 10, 2026

Welcome to MKP Support Electron (hereinafter referred to as the "Software" or "MKPSE")! 
This Software is a third-party visual desktop application developed by independent developer MuCoreBenC (hereinafter referred to as the "Developer"), based on the open-source project YZcat2023/MKPSupport. It aims to provide you with a more convenient interactive experience for 3D printing support surface post-processing.

Before installing or using the Software, please read this EULA carefully, especially the limitations of liability and hardware risk disclaimers (Section 3). By installing and using this Software, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by all terms of this Agreement.

1. Scope and Open Source Acknowledgment
1.1 Scope: This Agreement is a legal agreement between you and the Developer regarding your use of the Software.
1.2 Acknowledgment: The underlying Gcode processing algorithms, core parameter concepts, and data structures of this Software originate from the open-source project MKPSupport released by YZcat2023. We strictly adhere to the open-source spirit and express our deepest gratitude to the original author for their outstanding contribution to the 3D printing community.

2. License Grant and Restrictions
2.1 License Grant: The Developer grants you a personal, free, non-commercial, non-transferable, and non-exclusive license to install and use the Software.
2.2 Restrictions: You may not:
  (1) Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software;
  (2) Maliciously tamper with the Software or use it for any illegal purposes that may cause physical damage to 3D printing equipment.

3. Core Disclaimer (Strict Hardware Risk Warning)
3.1 Hardware Risks: You fully understand and agree that this Software involves direct modifications to your 3D printer's Z-axis offset, XY-axis offset, and post-processing Gcode scripts. These parameters directly dictate the physical movement trajectory of the printer nozzle.
3.2 Assumption of Risk: Incorrect parameter settings (such as excessive negative Z-axis compensation) are highly likely to cause the nozzle to scrape the print bed (bed crash), potentially leading to severe physical damage to the printhead assembly, heat bed, and other hardware. You must use this tool with extreme caution and simulate the Gcode before actual printing.
3.3 Disclaimer of Liability: TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, YOU ASSUME ALL RISKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES FOR ANY DIRECT OR INDIRECT CONSEQUENCES ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE (INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO HARDWARE DAMAGE, WASTED FILAMENT, PROPERTY LOSS, OR PERSONAL INJURY). THE DEVELOPER SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DAMAGES WHATSOEVER.

4. Data and Privacy
4.1 Local Execution: This Software operates primarily in your local environment. Your preset parameters and configurations are stored locally on your device.
4.2 Network Requests: The Software only initiates secure network requests to platforms like GitHub/Gitee when you manually check for updates. The Software DOES NOT collect, upload, or track any of your personally identifiable information or privacy data.

5. Updates and Maintenance
5.1 Right to Terminate: As a free, personal open-source project, the Developer makes no commitment to perpetual maintenance, feature updates, or long-term technical support. 
5.2 Third-Party Slicers: The Developer is not responsible for print failures caused by defects or API changes in third-party slicing software (e.g., Bambu Studio, OrcaSlicer).

6. Miscellaneous
6.1 "AS IS" Provision: THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT.

If you agree to the above terms, please click "I Agree" to continue the installation. Happy 3D Printing!